cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and specifically focuses on reducing domain shift in unsupervised scene adaptation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach to address this problem, which involves channel-wise feature alignment and leverages feature statistics, indicating that it could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with adapting models to real urban scenes, which suggests that it could be related to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
